davfs2: davfs2 (Mount a WebDAV resource as a regular file system.)
davfs2:
davfs2: Web Distributed Authoring and Versioning (WebDAV), an extension to
davfs2: the HTTP-protocol, allows authoring of resources on a remote web
davfs2: server. davfs2 provides the ability to access such resources like a
davfs2: typical filesystem, allowing for use by standard applications with no
davfs2: built-in support for WebDAV.
davfs2:
davfs2: http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/davfs2
davfs2:

